          "text": "This depends on your mortgage interest rate versus your expected investment return. If your mortgage rate is 3%, but you can earn 7% in the stock market, mathematically it makes sense to invest. However, paying off a mortgage provides a guaranteed return and significant emotional peace of mind that investing cannot offer."
